    "information_content_info_rLNFk9": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "richtext_MXBQD4": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>In India, for example, all jewelry and stones have distinct cultural, religious, and astrological properties which are said to offer protection, blessings, or to help designate the human energy into alignment with the infinite cosmos. These beliefs come close to the Western astrological system's reliance on interpreting aids for cosmic bodies as a possible predicted interpretation of human traits, fate, or occurrences. Astrological jewelry arose out of these powerful traditions and continues to thrive even today!<br/><br/>Just like Indian concepts of Rashi and Kundli, astrology uses the position of celestial bodies at the time of birth to predict important events in life, human nature, and exercise caution in certain aspects of life. Essentially, the year is divided into 12 periods, each period represented by an astrological sign (also known as a zodiac sign), which attempts to predict your character, strengths, and challenges. Every astrological sign or zodiac sign is ruled by planets and other cosmic elements that influence behaviour and destiny through cosmic forces, which can be balanced through certain gemstones and metals that resonate with the respective cosmic vibrations. These jewelry pieces are what’s known as zodiac jewelry, with pendant jewelry and gemstone rings being some of the most popular examples. <br/><br/>Astrological <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/all-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Rings\">rings</a>, zodiac pendants, and astrology <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/all-necklaces\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Necklaces\">necklaces</a> are extremely popular amongst people who believe in astrology, as they hold great cultural and traditional importance for the wearer. For instance, an individual who is challenged in his work might be told to wear a Blue Sapphire (astrological gemstone attributed to Saturn) in a jyotish ring. Brides typically receive <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/wedding-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Wedding Rings\">wedding rings</a> which serve as reflections of love, sentiment and commitment, and because diamonds are associated with Venus (the planet of love and harmony).  Embedding rubies and emeralds in <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-ring\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Engagement Rings\">engagement rings</a> is a common practice due to their aesthetic appeal and also because these gemstones are closely associated with prosperity and strength. Similarly, gemstone earrings and astrology pendants also feature astrological gemstones specifically chosen to balance emotions, improve confidence, and provide protection against negative and unexpected events. <br/><br/>Gemstones are frequently referred to as “tools of light” by astrologers. This comes from a Sanskrit tradition entitled \"Ratna Shastra\", which teaches that every gemstone vibrates at its unique frequency that is in sync with cosmic energies. By wearing the jewelry pieces on the body, the vibrations and frequencies of gemstones will blend with and affect your personal aura. <br/>Gemstone Rings with Manik, or Ruby, are said to bring vitality and leadership by strengthening the energies of the sun. <br/>Gemstone Pendants featuring Motis, or Pearls, are believed to induce tranquility and inner peace through the strengthening of lunar frequencies.<br/>Stylish gemstone earrings studded with Panna, or Emeralds, are believed to sharpen intellect, especially for Gemini and Virgo Zodiac Signs, by strengthening the frequencies of Mercury. <br/>In India, millions consider astrologers before purchasing gemstones even today. The West is also seeing a surge in the use of crystals and gemstones for prosperity, protection, and healing. <br/><br/>As Zodiac signs become an integral part of Millennial and Gen-Z culture, the demand for personalised zodiac jewelry is on a constant rise. Shoppers seek more stylish pieces that resonate with their personalities and zodiac signs. Each of the twelve zodiac signs - Aries, Taurus, Gemini, Cancer, Leo, Virgo, Libra, Scorpio, Sagittarius, Capricorn, Aquarius, and Pisces has recommended gemstones and jewelry styles. Wearing the correct zodiac pendants or zodiac earrings can go a long way in amplifying the strengths of the correct cosmic bodies while reducing the influence of negative energies.</p><ul><li> Aries may wear bold Aries jewelry or a bold Aries necklace with shimmering diamonds amplifying Mars’ frequencies. </li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Leo star sign jewellery amplifies the solar frequencies through the use of gold and peridots. </li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Capricorn pendants usually feature garnets and a platinum base to balance Saturn's discipline</li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Aquarius jewelry shines bright with a platinum base and an amethyst highlight, helping enhance an Aquarius’ progressive and analytical nature. <br/></li></ul><p></p><ul><li>White Gold and Platinum necklaces complement Pisces’ fluid and mystical energy, which is further enhanced by an Aquamarine centrestone.<br/></li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Stylish jewellery pieces studded with emerald help Taurus think clearly and stay patient. <br/></li></ul><p></p><ul><li>White Gold and Platinum sets with Pearls complement Gemini's airy and intellectual nature while boosting communication skills. <br/></li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Rubies symbolize love, passion, and strength, which matches the caring and warmth-giving nature of Cancers while Platinum and White Gold complement the sign’s connection to the water element and the moon. <br/></li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Blue Sapphire Jewellery protects Virgos from negative thoughts and helps them attract luck and prosperity.<br/></li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Jewellery embedded with Opal can be especially lucky Libras as the gemstone is not only considered to bring good luck and enhance emotional healing and well being. <br/></li></ul><p></p><ul><li>Jewelry made of topaz enriches Scorpio's strength, passion, and intuition while providing balance and clarity to their strong energy.<br/></li><li>Jewelry made of tanzanite amplifies Sagittarian nature of adventure and provides inspiration for focusing on wisdom, optimism, and spiritual growth at a deeper level.<br/></li></ul><p>Popular modern zodiac jewelry trends often feature bold zodiac symbols, merging spirituality and culture with contemporary fashion and self-expression. <br/><br/>Astrology and gemstones can also be applied to romantic relationships, encounters, and relationships in general. Relationship astrology is the branch of astrology that focuses on the strengths and weaknesses that may be reflected in the planetary charts of romantic partners and helps to determine compatibility. Based on the couple's birth chart and zodiac signs, we can then make a recommendation for a specific gemstone for their wedding and engagement rings for emotional understanding, financial balance, and long-lasting peace and prosperity in their romantic lives. In the realm of romance, zodiac and astrological jewelry can also serve as a representation of cosmic alignment in their romantic partnership. If you're in a relationship and your partner is an enthusiastic believer in astrology and the zodiac, consider giving them a zodiac sign pendant. These designs would almost certainly align with their personality much more!</p>"
          }
        }
      },
